response.Q0: Because it cost a lot of money to click on the nodes, I decided to only check the ones at the ends, and whenever I reached the highest, that is the node I would travel to with the spider.
response.Q1: Yes, I inspected the nodes and if I got any 80 and above, I stopped inspecting and just went to that one, because I figured that might be the highest node I would get and thus spend less money inspecting.
response.Q2: I was not that difficult one I figured out that any number in the +80s is probably the highest I was going to get, the tricky part was trying to guess where the number could be in that round, in light of where it was in the previous round, If I did find it.

response.Q0: At the beginning trying to understand the instructions was hard, in fact it is only now that I realize that there was a reward for clicking the first nodes. I saw it briefly, but I wasn't sure about it in any way.
response.Q1: No, I haven't participated in this before, it was actually fun, I would definitely remember if I had.
